LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) — A 14-year-old Lincoln boy has been accused of holding a handgun to a girl's head near a high school. Authorities say the boy is charged with terroristic threats and use of a deadly weapon to commit a felony. The Associated Press generally doesn't name juveniles accused of crimes. A police report says the 14-year-old girl reported that she and the boy began arguing behind a convenience store near Lincoln North Star High School last week. She says he took the semi-automatic pistol from his waistband, pulled back its slide and held the gun to her head. She told police he asked bystanders whether he ought to pull the trigger, and she pushed the gun away and left. No shot has been reported, and it's unclear whether the weapon was loaded. Latest from the SFGATE homepage:Click below for the top news from around the Bay Area and beyond. Sign up for our newsletters to be the first to learn about breaking news and more. Go to 'Sign In' and 'Manage Profile' at the top of the page. ALABAMA SENATE RACE Ex-colleague: 'Common knowledge' Moore 'dated high school girls' 'SNL' roasts Roy Moore over allegations Will Alabama pick a Democrat over Moore? LATEST NEWS Why Stanton would fit with Giants and one big reason he won't Mother marries her son and then her daughter, officials say 60,000 join far-right march in Poland Bay Area crews in wildfires to be tested for toxic chemicals Trump taunts Kim: 'I would NEVER call him short, fat' 49ers host Giants in historically awful matchup Disneyland visitors contract Legionnaires’ disease Demolition of Bay Bridge's old eastern span completed /*<![CDATA[*/ hearstPlaceAd("SP260"); /*]]>*/ The amazing tale of SF's most legendary, rat-killing dogs Rare, private photos of SF clawing back after 1906 quake Mid-century SF photos unseen for decades Underrated SF landmarks every local should visit at least once Warriors show their dominance in rout of 76ers Report: 3 UCLA players to stay in China Top 10 places in the West for a fami